  "image": "2082.png",
  "bookTitle": "Wandering Ghost",
  "bookId": 65,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A terrifying great white shark girl ghost who can lurk anywhere. She suddenly jumps out shouting 'Shark!' and bites people -- super scary.",
  "personality": "Always smiling, yet the warmth never reaches her eyes. She passively goes through many tasks without caring about the results.",
  "like": "Popsicles, sharks",
  "familiarData": "What's wrong with ghosts? Ghosts want to enjoy summer too, eat popsicles too, and wear swimsuits too.\nHowever, normal ghosts cannot walk under the sun. In winter when temperatures drop there's a chance, but the summer sun is the natural enemy of spirits -- impossible to venture outdoors.\n\nBut -- a ghost in a swimsuit is the exception.\n'As long as you wear a swimsuit, you can enjoy summer~' a mysterious voice told Sherry. After trying it, she indeed became a summer ghost unafraid of sunlight.\n\nThe tail is a magical tool that helps Sherry swim, allowing her to combine her ghost phasing ability with unobstructed free swimming. The tool has extremely high compatibility -- to her, it feels like her own tail.\nPerhaps it fits too well, as some shark ghosts even treat her as a real shark and gather around her. Sherry can use her own power to materialize these ghost sharks, making a horror-movie shark tornado a reality, but that takes too much energy, so she can only use it to scare people.\n\nCome to think of it, sharks, girl ghost, swimsuit, horror... it feels like too many tropes stacked together.\nDespite the many questionable elements, it really is cute. Kind of want to get bitten by this great white shark girl ghost.",
  "familiarUnlockLevel": 5,
